article.headline: Comets surge down the stretch
article.story:
SACRAMENTO, Calif. (AP) -- Sheryl Swoopes scored 29 points to
lead the Houston Comets to a 74-71 victory over the Sacramento
Monarchs on Saturday night.

Trailing 70-65 with 42 seconds left, Houston went on a 9-2 run.
The spurt was capped by Michelle Snow's rebound and subsequent
basket that erased Sacramento's 71-70 lead.

Swoopes made all 12 free throws, including two with 5.7 seconds
left that gave Houston a 74-71 lead. The All-Star forward scored 22
points in the second half and added eight rebounds and seven
assists.

Lady Grooms, who beat San Antonio on Thursday with a shot in the
closing seconds, missed a 3-point attempt at the end of Saturday's
game.

Tangela Smith scored 15 points, and DeMya Walker had 13 for
Sacramento. The Monarchs had won its first three games under
interim coach John Whisenant, who replaced Maura McHugh. Kara
Lawson added 11 points.

The Monarchs trailed most of the game but Ticha Penicheiro made
a rare 3-pointer to put Sacramento ahead with 1:40 remaining. On
their next possession, the Monarchs took a 70-65 lead when rookie
Kara Lawson made a 3-pointer.

Janeth Arcain scored 19 points, and Snow added 10 for Houston.
The Comets have won two straight and six of seven.

Houston's All-Star forward Tina Thompson watched the game in
street clothes due to a sore left ankle. She returned to the lineup
on Friday after a two-game absence and helped the Comets win in Los
Angeles.

Arcain and Snow scored eight points for the Comets, who led by
as many as 15 in the first half.
